<subSubSection id="CBED654DA91F6616FF4DF988FDAB9436" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="834836C6A91F6611FF4DF988FE8E936D" blockId="3.[189,310,1539,1565]" box="[189,310,1539,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="D80081AAA91F6611FF4DF988FE8E936D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1539,1565]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FF4DF988FE8E936D" bold="true" box="[189,310,1539,1565]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="834836C6A91F6616FF4DF9BAFDAB9436" blockId="3.[187,1401,1585,1964]" lastBlockId="4.[188,1399,265,327]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A91F6611FD57F9B9FBF6933B" authority="Du &amp; Wang, 2006" authorityName="Du &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2006" box="[679,1102,1585,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilongispina">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FD57F9B9FCD1933B" box="[679,873,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In. trilongispina</emphasis>
Du &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="E7664B37A91F6611FC4FF9B9FBF6933B" author="Wang Z. J. &amp; Du Y. Z. &amp; Sivec I. &amp; Li Z. Z." box="[959,1102,1585,1612]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="50 - 56" refId="ref3525" refString="Wang Z. J., Du Y. Z., Sivec I. &amp; Li Z. Z. 2006. Records and descriptions of some Nemouridae species (Order: Plecoptera) from Leigong Mountain, Guizhou province, China. Illiesia 2 (7): 50 - 56." type="journal article" year="2006">Wang, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="4133F824A91F6611FB6AF9BAFB47933B" box="[1178,1279,1585,1611]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
in having a similar epiproct and long spines on the paraproct, and also seems related to 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A91F6611FB67F9DDFA87931F" authorityName="Li, Wu &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2017" box="[1175,1343,1622,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvispina">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FB67F9DDFA87931F" box="[1175,1343,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In. curvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A91F6611FF4DF9F2FD8593E2" authority="Du &amp; Wang, 2009" authorityName="Du &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2009" box="[189,573,1656,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilateralia">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FF4DF9F2FED893E2" box="[189,352,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In. bilateralia</emphasis>
Du &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="E7664B37A91F6611FE40F9F3FD8593E2" author="Wang Z. J. &amp; Du Y. Z." box="[432,573,1656,1682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref3475" refString="Wang Z. J. &amp; Du Y. Z. 2009. Four new species of the genus Indonemoura (Plecoptera: Nemouridae) from China. Zootaxa 1976 (1): 56 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1976.1.4" type="journal article" year="2009">
Wang, 
<quantity id="440F9B23A91F6611FDF2F9F3FD8593E2" box="[514,573,1656,1682]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10286" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="in" value="2009.0">2009</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having a similar epiproct and hypoproct. However, the new species can be separated by the median lobe extending a long hamulus sclerotized bars, apex pointed, without other spines; outer lobe shorter than median lobe obviously and apex blunt rounded, with a tiny subapical spine; tip of hypoproct rounded. In 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A91F6611FDA5F969FCAA938B" authorityName="Du &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2006" box="[597,786,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilongispina">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FDA5F969FCAA938B" box="[597,786,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In. trilongispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, median lobe with a long sclerotized bar and bearing a subapical spine and slightly inwardly directed acute apex; outer lobe without spines and denticles; tip of hypoproct pointed (
<bibRefCitation id="E7664B37A91F6611FE32F8A3FD289232" author="Wang Z. J. &amp; Du Y. Z. &amp; Sivec I. &amp; Li Z. Z." box="[450,656,1832,1858]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="50 - 56" refId="ref3525" refString="Wang Z. J., Du Y. Z., Sivec I. &amp; Li Z. Z. 2006. Records and descriptions of some Nemouridae species (Order: Plecoptera) from Leigong Mountain, Guizhou province, China. Illiesia 2 (7): 50 - 56." type="journal article" year="2006">
Wang 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FDFFF8A2FDF29232" box="[527,586,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 8–9, 11); in 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A91F6611FCABF8A2FC469232" authorityName="Li, Wu &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2017" box="[859,1022,1833,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvispina">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FCABF8A2FC469232" box="[859,1022,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In. curvispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, apex of median lobe spine-like and bilobed, outer lobe with a larger apical spine at outer margin and a small, dorsal, subapical spine at proximal margin (Li 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FE47F8E4FE4B92F8" box="[439,499,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
2017: figs 1–2, 5); in 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A91F6611FD0BF8E4FC2792F8" authorityName="Du &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2009" box="[763,927,1902,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilateralia">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A91F6611FD0BF8E4FC2792F8" box="[763,927,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">In. bilateralia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, median lobe branched to two portions, inner portion membranous, outer portion forming a long, thin sclerotized bar with 3 or 4 prongs at tip; outer lobe much longer than median lobe, apex with a strong prong and a small lateral spine subapically (
<bibRefCitation id="E7664B37A9186616FF34FEA7FE219436" author="Wang Z. J. &amp; Du Y. Z." box="[196,409,300,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref3475" refString="Wang Z. J. &amp; Du Y. Z. 2009. Four new species of the genus Indonemoura (Plecoptera: Nemouridae) from China. Zootaxa 1976 (1): 56 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1976.1.4" type="journal article" year="2009">Wang &amp; Du 2009</bibRefCitation>
: figs 1–4).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBED654DA9186616FF4DFEE5FDCA94A9" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="834836C6A9186616FF4DFEE5FEFC94F8" blockId="4.[189,324,366,392]" box="[189,324,366,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading id="D80081AAA9186616FF4DFEE5FEFC94F8" bold="true" box="[189,324,366,392]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FF4DFEE5FEFC94F8" bold="true" box="[189,324,366,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="834836C6A9186616FF4DFE17FDCA94A9" blockId="4.[189,1398,412,474]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The name refers to the median lobe of paraproct with a long hamulus shape. The Latin ‘ 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FB0DFE17FA8194C6" box="[1277,1337,412,438]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">longi</emphasis>
’ and ‘ 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FF37FE34FEA794A9" box="[199,287,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">hamata</emphasis>
’ mean ‘long’ and ‘hamulus’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="D788664EA9186616FF4DF80AFDB89291" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619874" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6619874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619874/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" startId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" targetBox="[340,1247,595,1881]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="834836C6A9186616FF4DF80AFDB89291" blockId="4.[189,1399,1921,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FF4DF80AFEA892EB" bold="true" box="[189,272,1921,1947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A9186616FEEDF80AFD4592EB" authority="Bai &amp; Qian" authorityName="Bai &amp; Qian" authorityYear="2022" box="[285,765,1921,1947]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longihamata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FEEDF80AFDE792EB" box="[285,607,1921,1947]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Indonemoura longihamata</emphasis>
Bai &amp; Qian
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAB057AFA9186616FCF9F809FCD392EC" box="[777,875,1922,1948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, ♂ (SWFU). 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FB64F80AFB1192EB" bold="true" box="[1172,1193,1921,1947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A</emphasis>
. Habitus, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FEF6F82FFEA292CE" bold="true" box="[262,282,1956,1982]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">B</emphasis>
. Head and prothorax, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FD24F82FFD5F92CE" bold="true" box="[724,743,1956,1982]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. Terminalia, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FBD6F82FFB8192CE" bold="true" box="[1062,1081,1956,1982]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">D</emphasis>
. Terminalia, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9186616FF4FF843FF689292" bold="true" box="[191,208,1992,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E</emphasis>
. Terminalia, lateral view.
