<quantity id="440F9B23A9196617FB06FDBFFADA973E" box="[1270,1378,564,590]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.04" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.4">10.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="834836C6A9196617FF4DFDFDFC5A97C2" blockId="5.[189,1399,629,690]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
HEAD (
<figureCitation id="1BCC2A43A9196617FEE1FDFEFECA97FF" box="[273,370,629,656]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,595,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-68@4.[340,1247,582,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Indonemoura longihamata Bai &amp; Qian sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (SWFU). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head and prothorax, ventral view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. E. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619874/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Head light brown, three ocelli; compound eyes black and protruded; antennae light brown with abundant decumbent pubescence; mouthparts yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="834836C6A9196617FF4DFD51FB4D9667" blockId="5.[189,1399,730,792]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
THORAX (
<figureCitation id="1BCC2A43A9196617FEDCFD51FE179784" box="[300,431,730,756]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,595,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-68@4.[340,1247,582,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Indonemoura longihamata Bai &amp; Qian sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (SWFU). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head and prothorax, ventral view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. E. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619874/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Weak sclerotized. Pronotum slightly brown with rugosities; obvious nodules in cervical gills; legs lightly brown and with a brown narrowly band on the anterior of femora.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="834836C6A9196617FF4DFCB4FA809628" blockId="5.[189,1336,830,857]" box="[189,1336,830,857]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
WINGS (
<figureCitation id="1BCC2A43A9196617FEEBFCB5FEC19629" box="[283,377,830,857]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,595,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-68@4.[340,1247,582,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Indonemoura longihamata Bai &amp; Qian sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (SWFU). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head and prothorax, ventral view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. E. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619874/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Macropterous; wings brownish-yellow and membrane translucent, veins brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="834836C6A9196614FF4DFC0BFED69436" blockId="5.[187,1399,896,993]" lastBlockId="6.[188,1398,265,326]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation id="1BCC2A43A9196617FECCFC0BFE0096EA" box="[316,440,896,922]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,595,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-68@4.[340,1247,582,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Indonemoura longihamata Bai &amp; Qian sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (SWFU). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head and prothorax, ventral view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. E. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619874/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2A, C</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segments generally brownish-yellow and weakly sclerotized. Tergum 9 weakly sclerotized with a thin and transverse sclerite on mid-anterior margin. Tergum 10 weakly sclerotized, median concaved below epiproct, a transverse arc-shaped sclerite anteriorly, two irregular sclerites posteriorly and a triangular sclerites on the both sides. Cerci long, cylindrical and membranous, without spines.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D788664EA9196617FF4EF8F7FDD992AE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619876" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6619876" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619876/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" startId="5.[190,233,1916,1942]" targetBox="[189,1398,1086,1878]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="834836C6A9196617FF4EF8F7FDD992AE" blockId="5.[189,1399,1916,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9196617FF4EF8F7FEB692E6" bold="true" box="[190,270,1916,1942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
Habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A9196617FE6BF8F6FC3992E7" authority="Bai &amp; Qian" authorityName="Bai &amp; Qian" authorityYear="2022" box="[411,897,1917,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yingjiangensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9196617FE6BF8F6FD5792E6" box="[411,751,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Indonemoura yingjiangensis</emphasis>
Bai &amp; Qian
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAB057AFA9196617FC7AF8F6FC5F92E7" box="[906,999,1917,1943]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44F74D45A9196617FBD5F8F6FACE92E7" authority="Bai &amp; Qian" authorityName="Bai &amp; Qian" authorityYear="2022" box="[1061,1398,1917,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Indonemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longihamata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9196617FBD5F8F6FB5C92E7" box="[1061,1252,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">In. longihamata</emphasis>
Bai &amp; Qian
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAB057AFA9196617FF4FF82BFEA292CA" box="[191,282,1952,1978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in Tongbiguan Provincial Nature Reserve. 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9196617FCEEF82BFC8B92CA" bold="true" box="[798,819,1952,1978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A</emphasis>
. The upper reaches of unknown streams. 
<emphasis id="B183EAD4A9196617FAD7F82BFA8292CA" bold="true" box="[1319,1338,1952,1978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">B</emphasis>
. The lower reaches of unknown streams.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="834836C6A91A6614FF4DFEE5FC889798" blockId="6.[187,1400,366,744]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
GENITALIA (
<figureCitation id="1BCC2A43A91A6614FEB1FEE5FE0594F8" box="[321,445,366,392]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,595,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-68@4.[340,1247,582,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Indonemoura longihamata Bai &amp; Qian sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (SWFU). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Head and prothorax, ventral view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. E. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6619874" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6619874/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2C–E</figureCitation>
). Vesicle of sternum 9 mostly membranous, oval-shaped, apex rounded. Hypoproct exceptionally long and broad, apex gradually narrowed, forming a linguiform shaped sclerite. Epiproct narrowed, lightly enlarged in median portion, dorsal sclerites mostly membranous, with two triangular sclerites in the middle extending ventral surface, apex with a small notch mid-anteriorly; basal of epiproct narrowed and slightly sclerotized in lateral view, elevated at ⅓ of terminal, apex weakly upward; ventral sclerites expanded into a large arched-shaped and strong sclerotized ridges, fringed with some tiny spines. Paraproct divided into three lobes in ventral view, inner lobe short and covered by hypoproct, closely connected to the median lobe; median lobe broad basally in ventral view, and extending a long hamulus sclerotized bars, apex pointed in lateral view; outer lobe basal part elongated and recurved dorsally alongside cerci, terminal part slenderly sclerotized bar and apex blunt rounded in lateral view, shorter than median lobe, with a subapical tiny spine.
</paragraph>
